cs.THEORY, cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.CG. 

The paper deals with theoretical aspects of self-assembly models and their universality, which suggests cs.THEORY as the most likely sub-category. The use of tile-based models and their transformations also suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as possible sub-categories. The paper also involves computational geometry and simulations, which could fall under cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
